3 Plot


dimred_profile <-
  function(profiles,
           method = "umap",
           metric = "euclidean") {
    stopifnot(method %in% c("pca", "umap"))
    
    metadata <- get_annotation(profiles) %>% select(-id)

    data_matrix <- drop_annotation(profiles)
    
    if (method == "umap") {
      
      umap_config <- umap::umap.defaults
      
      umap_config$metric <- metric
      
      umap_config$random_state <- 123
      
      umap_obj <- umap::umap(data_matrix, config = umap_config)
      
      dimred_df <- data.frame(umap_obj$layout)
      
      
    } else if (method == "pca") {
      
      pca_obj <- prcomp(data_matrix)
      
      dimred_df <- data.frame(pca_obj$x[,1:10])
      
    }
    
    
    df <-
      bind_cols(metadata,
                dimred_df)
    df
  }

3.1 Plot DMSOs

dmso_pca <- dimred_profile(dmso_profiles, method = "pca")

ggplot(dmso_pca,
       aes(PC1, PC2, color = Metadata_Plate)) + geom_point()

variables <-
  names(dmso_profiles) %>% str_subset("Metadata_", negate = TRUE)

dmso_spherized <-
  cytominer::whiten(
    population = dmso_profiles,
    variables = variables,
    sample = dmso_profiles,
    regularization_param = 1e-5
  )

dmso_pca <- dimred_profile(dmso_spherized, method = "pca")

ggplot(dmso_pca %>% filter(PC1 > -1 & PC2 < 2),
       aes(PC1, PC2, color = Metadata_Plate)) + geom_point()


dmso_outliers <-
  dmso_pca %>% filter(PC1 < -1 |
                        PC2 > 2) %>% select(Metadata_Plate, Metadata_Well)

dmso_cleaned_profiles <- dmso_profiles %>% anti_join(dmso_outliers)
Joining, by = c("Metadata_Plate", "Metadata_Well")
dmso_cleaned_spherized_profiles <-
  cytominer::whiten(
    population = dmso_cleaned_profiles,
    variables = variables,
    sample = dmso_cleaned_profiles,
    regularization_param = 1e-5
  )

dmso_cleaned_pca <- dimred_profile(dmso_cleaned_spherized_profiles, method = "pca")

ggplot(dmso_cleaned_pca,
       aes(PC1, PC2, color = Metadata_Plate)) + geom_point()

4 Transform

profiles_spherized <-
  cytominer::whiten(
    population = profiles,
    variables = variables,
    sample = dmso_profiles,
    regularization_param = 1e-5
  )

ggplot(profiles_spherized %>% sample_frac(1),
       aes(PC1, PC2, color = Metadata_Plate)) + geom_point() +
  ggtitle(glue("{experiment_tag}: spherizing using original data"))


profiles_spherized <-
  cytominer::whiten(
    population = profiles,
    variables = variables,
    sample = dmso_cleaned_profiles,
    regularization_param = 1e-5
  )

ggplot(profiles_spherized %>% sample_frac(1),
       aes(PC1, PC2, color = Metadata_Plate)) + geom_point() +
  ggtitle(glue("{experiment_tag}: spherizing using cleaned data"))
